Steps:
[ACT] Open browser DevTools Network tab and start recording before navigation
[NAV] Navigate to {{FRONT_URL}}/search?q=@td(SEARCH_CLOTHING.query)
[WAIT] Wait for search results page to load and POST /graphql (searchProducts) to settle
[ASSERT] Verify at least 1 product card rendered in results grid
[SETUP] browser_snapshot the first product card; capture displayed name → {dom_name}; capture displayed price string → {dom_price_str}
[SETUP] inspect the most-recent POST /graphql (searchProducts) response; capture items[0].name → {api_name}; capture items[0].price.actual.amount → {api_price_num}; capture items[0].price.actual.formattedAmount (or equivalent) → {api_price_str}
[LOG] write {dom_name, dom_price_str, api_name, api_price_num, api_price_str} to evidence
[ASSERT] Verify {dom_name} equals {api_name}
[ASSERT] Verify the numeric value parsed from {dom_price_str} equals {api_price_num} (no rounding drift)

Assertions:
[DOM] First product card name equals API items[0].name exactly
[MATH] Numeric parse of {dom_price_str} equals {api_price_num}
[STATE] No data transformation errors between API response and UI rendering
[DOM] Product image on card is loaded (not broken placeholder)
[STATE] {api_price_num} > 0 and is formatted with 2 decimals in {dom_price_str}

Title:
[MATH] Inclusion window [{boundary_lo} TO {boundary_hi}] contains the captured product {picked_pdp_name}
[MATH] Every product visible under inclusion window has price within [{boundary_lo}, {boundary_hi}] inclusive
[MATH] Exclusion window [{boundary_hi} TO …] excludes the captured product
[MATH] Every product visible under exclusion window has price >= {boundary_hi}
[NAV] URL reflects facets=\price\":[N TO M] notation for both states

Steps:
[NAV] Navigate to {{FRONT_URL}}
[SETUP] read test-data/search-queries/b2b-buyer-queries.csv, filter rows where query_type=broad-noun AND expected_min_results>=2, pick a random row → {picked_query}
[LOG] write {picked_query} to evidence
[ACT] Click the search input
[ACT] fill 'Search': {picked_query}
[KEY] press [Enter]
[WAIT] Wait for /search?q=… results page
[SETUP] capture the initial result count (from heading) → {count_broad}
[ASSERT] Verify {count_broad} >= 2 (broad search returned multiple results to refine)
[LOG] append {count_broad} to evidence
[SETUP] browser_snapshot the facet sidebar; pick a random facet group with >=2 values and where the first value has count >0 → {picked_facet_group, picked_facet_value}
[ACT] Click {picked_facet_value} in {picked_facet_group}
[WAIT] Wait for filtered results
[SETUP] capture the filtered result count → {count_after_facet}
[LOG] append {picked_facet_group, picked_facet_value, count_after_facet} to evidence
[ASSERT] Verify {count_after_facet} <= {count_broad} (facet narrowed or held)
[ASSERT] Verify a filter chip for {picked_facet_value} is present in the chip bar
[ACT] Open the sort dropdown; select 'Price: Low to High'
[WAIT] Wait for products to reorder
[SETUP] capture the first 3 visible product card prices as numerics → {p1, p2, p3}
[LOG] append {p1, p2, p3} to evidence
[ASSERT] Verify p1 <= p2 <= p3 (ascending price ordering held under combined search + facet + sort)
[SETUP] capture the first card's name → {picked_pdp_name}
[ACT] Click the first product card
[WAIT] Wait for PDP to load
[ASSERT] Verify the PDP heading contains {picked_pdp_name}

[NAV] Navigate to {{FRONT_URL}}/catalog
[WAIT] Wait for catalog page + facet sidebar to load
[SETUP] browser_snapshot the facet sidebar; pick a facet group with >=2 values each with count >0 → {picked_facet_group}; capture the first two values as {val_A, val_B} with counts {count_A, count_B}
[LOG] write {picked_facet_group, val_A, count_A, val_B, count_B} to evidence
[SETUP] capture the initial result count (no filters applied) → {count_all}
[ACT] Click {val_A} in {picked_facet_group}
[WAIT] Wait for filtered results
[SETUP] capture filtered count → {count_only_A}
[ASSERT] Verify a chip for {val_A} appears; result count = {count_only_A} <= {count_all}
[ACT] Click {val_B} in the same {picked_facet_group} (DO NOT remove {val_A}; both should be active)
[WAIT] Wait for re-filtered results
[SETUP] capture re-filtered count → {count_A_or_B}
[LOG] append {count_only_A, count_A_or_B} to evidence
[ASSERT] Verify chips for BOTH {val_A} and {val_B} are present in the chip bar
[ASSERT] Verify {count_A_or_B} >= {count_only_A} (OR-within-group: adding a second value within the same group widens the result set; never narrows it)
[ASSERT] Verify {count_A_or_B} <= {count_all} (still constrained by the facet group)
[SETUP] sample 3 visible product cards' relevant attribute (e.g. Color if Color facet selected); count how many match {val_A}, how many match {val_B}, how many match neither → {n_A, n_B, n_neither}
[ASSERT] Verify {n_neither} == 0 (every visible product matches at least one of the selected values)

[NAV] Navigate to {{FRONT_URL}}/catalog
[WAIT] Wait for catalog + facet sidebar
[SETUP] capture initial result count → {count_initial}
[SETUP] pick a value from facet group 1 → {fg1_value}; pick a value from facet group 2 → {fg2_value}
[LOG] write {count_initial, fg1_value, fg2_value} to evidence
[ACT] Apply {fg1_value}
[WAIT] Wait for filtered results
[SETUP] capture count → {count_fg1_only}
[ACT] Apply {fg2_value}
[WAIT] Wait for results
[SETUP] capture count → {count_both}
[LOG] append {count_fg1_only, count_both} to evidence
[ASSERT] Verify chip bar shows both chips; result count = {count_both} <= {count_fg1_only} <= {count_initial}
[ACT] Path A — Chip-by-chip removal: click the close (×) on the {fg2_value} chip
[WAIT] Wait for results
[SETUP] capture count → {count_after_chip_removal}
[ASSERT] Verify the {fg2_value} chip is removed; {fg1_value} chip is still present; {count_after_chip_removal} equals {count_fg1_only} (restoring to single-facet state)
[ACT] Re-apply {fg2_value} to restore the two-chip state
[WAIT] Wait for results
[ASSERT] Verify count = {count_both} again
[ACT] Path B — Reset filters: click the 'Reset filters' button
[WAIT] Wait for results
[SETUP] capture count → {count_after_reset}
[ASSERT] Verify all chips removed from the chip bar
[ASSERT] Verify {count_after_reset} == {count_initial} (back to baseline)
